answer_html: A set \(S\) is countable if there exists a bijection (or a one to one correspondence) between \(S\) and \(\mathbb{N}\).
answer_latex:
A set $S$ is countable if there exists a bijection (or a one to one
correspondence) between $S$ and $\mathbb{N}$.
